147
00:32:11.540 --> 00:32:29.129
terence: sign the authorization from the validator side, and then send it to get the bid, yeah? And so basically, we have this implemented and tested, but there's one… I guess one lesson that we have learned along the way is that the identity

148
00:32:29.130 --> 00:32:37.590
terence: and the transport should be separate, because one of the first feedback we got was from the CommitBoost team. Basically.

149
00:32:37.590 --> 00:32:54.390
