150
00:32:54.390 --> 00:32:58.400
terence: to be the builder's URL. So, in a way, it has to

151
00:32:58.400 --> 00:33:16.569
terence: Pass through, basically. Otherwise, the builders will just reject them. And then commit boosts or any proxy, they don't hold… they don't have the validator key, so therefore they cannot sign, right? So we basically are coming to some sort of, discussion or feedback loop.

152
00:33:16.570 --> 00:33:23.409
terence: With the auto protocol ecosystem, like sidecars, like MOS, DVTs, so definitely.

153
00:33:23.410 --> 00:33:40.320
